thread.title: Kylie Minogue beats Kylie Jenner in battle to trademark name
thread.title_full: Kylie Minogue beats Kylie Jenner in battle to trademark name

author: Amy Croffey
title: Kylie Minogue beats Kylie Jenner in battle to trademark name
text:
Kylie Minogue has successfully blocked Kylie Jenner from trademarking the name "Kylie". Photo: Michael Dodge 
It dubbed Jenner as "a secondary reality television personality" and Minogue as an "internationally-renowned performing artist, humanitarian and breast cancer activist known to the world simply as Kylie". 
The US Patent Office has sided with Minogue, but Jenner is said to be planning an appeal. Advertisement 
In the same week Minogue announced her split from fiance, Joshua Sasse , 29, it's good news for the Locomotion singer, but the Kardashians/Jenners don't go down easily without a fight. They might have their on-air spats but when an outsider threatens the family business, they speak with one voice. 
In December, it was revealed that Kardashian West and her sisters, Kourtney and Khloe Kardashian, are trying to stop their sister-in-law-to-be Blac Chyna (real name Angela Renee White) from trademarking the Kardashian name. SHARE
